<div class="container" style="padding-top: 50px;">
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h1>Tell us everything.</h1>
    <p>Wait But Why is a microblogging and social media platform that allows users to tell a story about their life via a timeline of events. Sort of an off-beat LinkedIn. Users have posts called Events about their life where they did something - anything really. However, in contrast to LinkedIn where one details the accomplishments or growth of a life episode, users will explain why the episode happened, using one of three tags: “It was something I wanted to do”, “I felt like I had to”, or “I had no control over it”, and then further providing a description with their thoughts on the event.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
<form {{action 'newEvent' on='submit'}}>
  <h5>Something you did:</h5>
  {{input placeholder='e.g. I gave up on my dream of being a hip hop dancer.' value=event.title}}
  {{!-- <h5>When?</h5>
  {{input placeholder='e.g. 20171230' value=event.date}} --}}

<h5>When?</h5>
<div class="row">
